<br>
Here I am in Split Paw, doing the bard thing.  Having just recently gotten my mez and charm songs, I'm working on doing crowd control.  Basically, this involves the following progression:<br>
<br>
1) When &quot;add&quot; jumps on healer, switch out the weapons for a mino horn and play mez.  Just as it hits, watch primary tank begin smacking &quot;add&quot;, rendering what you're doing useless.<br>
<br>
2) Next time, try charm instead.  When &quot;add&quot; arrives, just target it and sing the charm song.  Watch &quot;add&quot; resist the charm song and come beat the snot out of the bard.<br>
<br>
3) After gently suggesting to tanks that they let you protect the healer, have horn equipped.  When &quot;add&quot; arrives, target it and mez it.  Watch panicked casters nuke mezzed &quot;add&quot;.<br>
<br>
4) Forget mez.  Equip the horn and try charm.  Successfully charm the &quot;add&quot; and have it beat the snot out of the primary tank's mob.  Jump up and down in glee for 17 seconds then watch BOTH mobs come to beat the snot out of the bard.<br>
<br>
I'd worked my way through to number four, and was bleeding profusely and congratulating myself for being so uber and awesome as to be able to charm a blue mob for a nanosecond.  As I was recouperating, I get this blob of purple text:<br>
<br>
Rogue001 tells you, 'Can you take some stuff?  I'm out of space.'<br>
<br>
You tell Rogue001, 'I'm short on space too.  I can take weight, but not bulk.'<br>
<br>
Then, a trade window appears.  There's a couple of big things.  Then, all sorts of group text starts scrolling by, so I hit 'TRADE'.  (Rogue001 might have Muahaahaa'd... who knows.) As it turns out, the group stuff was:<br>
<br>
&quot;Incoming a Tsech Mal Gnoll&quot; <br>
&quot;Add!&quot;  <br>
&quot;Add!&quot;<br>
<br>
Now for those of you with a bard alt, you know where this is going.  For those of you lacking a shiny blue high-visibility alt: bards dual wield.  Instruments cannot be equipped when you have a weapon equipped.  Consequently, equipping a horn requires taking two weapons out and putting one instrument in.  If you had n things in general inventory before, you now have n+1.  <br>
<br>
Unless, of course, you don't have any free inventory spots.  And since the last patch, if you receive things in trade that you would drop, they go on your pointer - you then have n+2 things after equipping an instrument.<br>
<br>
At that moment, trusting his bard to perform crowd control heroics, the primary tank shows up with gnolls (plural.)  I have weapons equipped, no free inventory spaces, and a fine steel rapier or some Split Paw armor thing on the end of my pointer.  I need my mino horn, and I need it now.<br>
<br>
What do I do?!?<br>
<br>
1) Frantically start opening bags and looking for something to dump.  Try to find the horn.  Panic.  Move food to bag, move horn to backpack.  Put level 29 song in backpack and put wooden flute in bag.  Move n+1 things around in n inventory spaces, exploring new inventory configurations.  Turn around in circles trying to count gnolls with bag and backpack open, having trouble seeing anything at all. <br>
<br>
2) Listen to barbarian-getting-chopped-up sounds and the occasional grunt of an Iksar getting clobbered.<br>
<br>
3) Start trying to drop something.<br>
<br>
&quot;Are you SURE you want to drop your Lute of the Gypsy Princess on the Ground?&quot;<br>
<br>
4) Cancel!<br>
<br>
5) Click click click.  A npc trade box opens up: it shows my Blade of Fiery Lamentations being handed to a Tesch Mal Gnoll.<br>
<br>
6) Cancel!<br>
<br>
7) Listen to screams from a wood elf female druid getting smacked around.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Click click click.  Get a loot item - any loot item! - on pointer.  Turn around, trying to face wall.  Wonder where the wall is, since it cannot be seen with bag and backpack open.<br>
<br>
9) Listen to Primary_tank tell the group, &quot;Help?&quot; Try to click on the floor to drop loot.  Watch a trade window open.  Offer a Split Paw Hide mask to Primary_tank.  Wait for him to hit cancel.<br>
<br>
10) Give up on moving things around.  Hit F8.  Play a song.  Anything.  Charm wrong mob.  <br>
<br>
11) Tell the group, &quot;Crud!  Wrong mob, sorry.&quot;  Consider turning off computer and feigning LD.<br>
<br>
12) Watch gnolls beat on each other.  Watch group barely survive.  Endure long, long silence after combat.  <br>
<br>
Now, I'm sure that Rogue001 didn't intend for this to happen.  But wouldn't it be ironic if he had an alt who tended to get encumbered and I had an alt who was always pestering him to hand me stuff? <br>
<br>
It must be karma.<br>
<br>
Cheers,<br>
<br>
Harmonae &quot;Is that a promise or a threat?&quot; Brooksong<br>
Blueberry bard of 27th Song<br>
